&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;High Intensity Psychological Therapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time - 37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dudley and Walsall IAPT Units&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Black Country Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust and is committed to improving health and wellbeing, tackling inequalities and providing high quality, responsive and efficient services within the Improving Access to Psychological Therapies (IAPT) guidelines. The IAPT programme supports the frontline NHS in implementing National Institute for Health and Clinical Excellence (NICE) guidelines for people with Depression and Anxiety. The team offers a range of psychological therapies to treat people and bring them to recovery using a system of stepped care. An exciting opportunity has arisen to recruit 2 Qualified High Intensity CBT Therapists to support the ongoing developments of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking highly motivated individuals who will be expected to demonstrate competence and have experience working in mental health services. They are also expected to commit themselves to the ongoing clinical supervision and case management essential to setting up and managing stepped care systems. They must be able to demonstrate that they have a strong commitment to high quality client care, good organisational skills, can prioritise their workload and have excellent communication abilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your enthusiasm, hard work and commitment you will benefit from being part of an expanding service that has common aims and goals, respects each other’s differences and always has the wellbeing of the individual at the centre of all practice. There will be an ongoing commitment to help you develop your skills within the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDominic DuttonAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Marcus Leonard on 07827 836720 or Walsall talking therapies on 01922 607535 for any queries regarding the vacancy.&lt;/p&gt;
